Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.53,0:00:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,[Dave Chappelle] This... is... surreal.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.09,0:00:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,[cheering and applause]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.92,0:00:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1987...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.54,0:00:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,1987, I moved back...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.17,0:00:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,from Ohio to D.C.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.06,0:00:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And-- and-- and enrolled\Nin Eastern High School,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.72,0:00:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,-and did...\N-[audience member] Whoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.93,0:00:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You must not have went there\Nwhen I went there, champ.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.24,0:01:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Those were tough times\Nis the way I remember it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.20,0:01:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,[chuckles]
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.48,0:01:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,[groans]
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.79,0:01:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,When I had gone, I-- I had\Nlived with my father for three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.15,0:01:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to middle school in Ohio,\Nand when I'd gotten back to Washington,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.37,0:01:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the crack epidemic was in full swing,\Nand the city was
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.26,0:01:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,largely unrecognizable to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.71,0:01:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I was an older kid, and-- and--\Nand kids my age were doing a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.34,0:01:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,wild things that I-- I didn't know\Nthat kids would do.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.96,0:01:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I-- I'd never seen a kid\Nwith a pager before,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.48,0:01:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know anything about\Nselling drugs, any of that shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.93,0:01:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All I knew, every day when I went\Nto Eastern, I didn't feel safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.90,0:01:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,[groans]
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.87,0:01:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a quiet guy, naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.00,0:01:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a shy person, naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.04,0:01:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And I used to get my
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.17,0:02:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,hair cut on a barbershop\Non 15th Street Northeast.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.76,0:02:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And I would go there, and, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.46,0:02:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and everyone in the barbershop\Nwould just snap on each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.96,0:02:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd sit in the corner,\Nand I-- and I'd watch everybody,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.88,0:02:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and just listen to all these jokes.\NThe guys were funny as shit,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.84,0:02:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but-- but one day,\Nafter a few weeks of goin' there
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.36,0:02:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and gettin' my hair cut,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.77,0:02:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,they-- they-- they turned the jokes on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.44,0:02:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I call that day The Barbershop Massacre.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.33,0:02:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I lit everybody in that barbershop up,\NI had been sittin' in there
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.44,0:02:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,listening to 'em for weeks\Ntalk about each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.12,0:02:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew every inside joke about each\Nand every one of 'em,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.75,0:02:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and they couldn't believe\NI knew this stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.66,0:02:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I lit their asses up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.96,0:02:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,From then on in the neighborhood,\Npeople kind of liked me, like, "Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.43,0:02:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,he's pretty funny."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.02,0:02:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Time magazine released an article\Nabout Bill Cosby.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.02,0:03:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The headline said,\N"Fifty, Funny, and Filthy Rich,"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.56,0:03:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and I read that article and it was\Nwhen I was looking at his face,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.43,0:03:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,before all that disgrace,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.44,0:03:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that I looked and I said,\N"I could do that."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.37,0:03:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I told my father and my father said,\N"Well, then just do it."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.69,0:03:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, "Well, I wouldn't even know\Nwhere to start," and he said,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.40,0:03:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,"Well, look in the phone book."\NIt's before the internet, if you're young.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.50,0:03:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We used to have a book\Nwith phone numbers in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.59,0:03:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,My father found for me the local\Ncomedy club in Washington, D.C.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.18,0:03:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I called 'em...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.27,0:03:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I found out when Open Mic night was,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.40,0:03:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and I started to go there\Non Tuesday nights... and just watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.15,0:03:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And then one night I went on a weekend.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.65,0:03:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I would-- I would get my money together\Nand I would go to this comedy club
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.53,0:03:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and I would just watch these comedians,\Nand sometimes...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.25,0:03:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes they would talk to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.71,0:04:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And I told one of the comedians\Nafter the show one night, I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.59,0:04:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,"Man, I really wanna try to do this."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.91,0:04:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And-- and he said, "Well..." He said...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.05,0:04:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, "If you wanna be a good comedian,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.30,0:04:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you should know how to act."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.21,0:04:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, "Why?" And he says, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.56,0:04:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't explain it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.88,0:04:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, "Okay," and I told my parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.23,0:04:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and-- and this is how I came to find out\Nabout Duke Ellington. My mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.89,0:04:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,she said, "There's a place you can go\Nwhere you can learn to act
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.27,0:04:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,right in Washington. It's a-- It's a high\Nschool." I said, "You mean I would...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.19,0:04:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,get out of Eastern?"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.17,0:04:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The school year was already in full swing\Nand Ellington has a policy that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.37,0:04:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't let people just come\Nin the middle of the year,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.70,0:04:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,but Lynda Gravatt was the head\Nof the theater department at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.00,0:04:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Very graciously took a meeting\Nwith me and my mother, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.76,0:05:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I get emotional thinking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.81,0:05:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody that went here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.61,0:05:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,[crowd cheers]
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.62,0:05:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember what it was first like?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.27,0:05:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,-[audience members] Yes! Yes!\N-When you first walked through the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.75,0:05:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It was in the afternoon, and everyone\Nwas in their arts classes,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.82,0:05:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and the girls had tutus on,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.20,0:05:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and everyone was weird, and walking around\Nthe hallway, like, you weren't sure
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.37,0:05:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,where anyone was supposed to be,\Nand you could hear people
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.55,0:05:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,practicing their horns and shit\Nall through the hallways.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.75,0:05:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There was art bouncing off the walls,\Nthe minute I walked through the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.81,0:05:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,there was a gallery of--\Nof all these children's work
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.93,0:05:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and these pictures were amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.14,0:05:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,My first thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.91,0:05:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,when I walked through that door:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.87,0:06:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'm not good enough to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.99,0:06:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.07,0:06:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And Miss Gravatt sat me down,\Nshe told me about the school,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.04,0:06:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and you remember Miss Gravatt?\NShe was very businesslike.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.87,0:06:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But also very warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.08,0:06:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,She was intimidating,\Nbut palpably kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.30,0:06:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,She was a paradox\Nof a human being.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.68,0:06:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,She gave me a date\Nfor an audition.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.73,0:06:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother said, "Okay, Dave,\Nit's on you." Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.14,0:06:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of you who know me...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.43,0:06:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,know that I didn't prepare\Nfor that audition.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.81,0:06:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That audition was like a-- a possession,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.12,0:06:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it was just something\Nthat I was proud to have.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.50,0:06:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But as the days got closer, I'm like,\N"Oh, my God, I gotta get--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.25,0:06:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I gotta get something together." I didn't\Neven know how to do an audition,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.92,0:06:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had never done it before, so I went\Nand I said-- I said, "What do I need?"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.37,0:07:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They said, "A monologue," I...\NSo I looked up "monologue."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.38,0:07:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And I went to the library,\Nthe MLK Library, this huge library,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.81,0:07:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,so I gotta find something,\Nand I found a piece
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.39,0:07:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in one of those yellow script books,\Nit was a monologue by Mark Twain
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.64,0:07:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,called "The Judge's Spirited Woman."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.24,0:07:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And I learned it in a night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.32,0:07:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it was not hard\Nfor me to memorize things.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.29,0:07:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The next day, it was a Saturday, I think,\Nand I came to the school,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.12,0:07:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and they auditioned in what used\Nto be this room-- the original...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.08,0:07:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,theater, Duke Ellington School\Nof the Arts.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.08,0:07:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And all the department heads sat in here,\Nand the light's in your eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.93,0:07:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's a bunch of kids who already\Ngo to the school, who come on Saturday,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.73,0:07:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,just to see...\Nwho might be coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.27,0:07:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And I talked to all these kids before\NI went in, and these kids
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.11,0:08:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,were nothing like the kids at Eastern.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.61,0:08:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They were like them, but they were\Ndifferent, they were weird,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.49,0:08:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,funny, and self-deprecating,\Nthings like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.75,0:08:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember\NI came out on stage...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.83,0:08:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and I did my audition,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.67,0:08:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was like...\Nlike, terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.50,0:08:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I-- I froze up in the beginning,\NI started, and then I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.73,0:08:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,"Wait a minute, I'm messing up,\NI'm gonna start again." [sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.35,0:08:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was nervous, and I was scared,\Nand... and...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.61,0:08:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in the middle of the audition,\NI'm in the middle of the monologue,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.27,0:08:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, one of the teachers, Fred Lee,\Nhe said-- Fred Lee, he goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.45,0:08:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,"Okay, that's enough."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.02,0:08:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, "Well, there's still a little\Nmore," he goes, "No, no, no, no, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.49,0:08:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That is enough," he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.96,0:08:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And I-- I can't tell you,\Nlike, I-- I was crushed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.66,0:09:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... without saying his disapproval,\NI knew it stunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.50,0:09:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was right.\NWhen I walked in here, I knew
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.80,0:09:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't good enough\Nto go to this school.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.19,0:09:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought to myself, "Ah, fuck\Nthis school, that's stupid anyway."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.74,0:09:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In first-year theater, there's a question\Nthat they ask students from time to time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.12,0:09:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's a make-or-break question, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.53,0:09:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And we ask this question,\Nyou don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.16,0:09:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And the question is this:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.75,0:09:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, "Why do you wanna act?"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.66,0:09:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.84,0:09:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,if you say anything like,\N"I wanna be a star,"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.25,0:09:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.79,0:09:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not gonna get in.\NI didn't know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.38,0:09:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And I figured I already blew the audition,\Nso I told them the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.48,0:09:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, "Why do you wanna act?"\N"I don't."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.07,0:10:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.61,0:10:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And they said, "Well then,\Nwhy are you here?"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.36,0:10:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, "Because I wanna be a comedian and\Nsome comedian told me that if I wanna be
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.65,0:10:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,a good comedian,\NI need to learn how to act."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.40,0:10:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And the teachers look\Nat each other and go,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.83,0:10:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,"Thank you very much," and I left.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.12,0:10:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was walking down the hallway\Nkicking rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.04,0:10:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a kid that already went here,\Nhis name was Ako Handy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.38,0:10:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And Ako said, "Hey, man, I listened\Nto them talking about you."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.01,0:10:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, "You did?" He said, "You're in."\NI said, "What?" He said, "You're in."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.36,0:10:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But it didn't make any sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.19,0:10:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow we worked it out so that\Nthey gave me an early enrollment,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.27,0:10:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and I left Eastern within weeks of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.24,0:10:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and I came to Duke Ellington and it was\Nbetter than I could have ever imagined.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.25,0:11:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't have the suspicion\Nthat most new kids get.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.12,0:11:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I was an oddity, a new toy, I was quirky,\NI wasn't a snappy dresser,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.87,0:11:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't really know\Nwhat the fuck was going on, because
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.29,0:11:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the crack epidemic itself was new to me
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.22,0:11:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and they were all refugees\Nfrom their neighborhood schools.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.11,0:11:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In the morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.11,0:11:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,we would have our academic classes,\Nand then in the afternoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.08,0:11:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we would have our arts classes.\NIt was a long school day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.62,0:11:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd start at 8:30, we wouldn't leave\Nhere 'til five, sometimes 5:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.62,0:11:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever they saw fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.62,0:11:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's funny walking in here tonight,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.13,0:11:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,'cause I saw the Pride flags up,\Nand I remember when I came here
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.55,0:11:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,all those years ago, it's the first time I\Never met a kid who was just, like, gay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.39,0:12:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,-It was never strange to us.\N-[woman in audience] That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.86,0:12:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Their sexuality or their gender identity
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.94,0:12:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,was the least remarkable thing about
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.20,0:12:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,a person that could dance as well\Nas Roger Bellamy, or...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.45,0:12:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no distinction\Nbetween any of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.91,0:12:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was weird\Nin their own way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.41,0:12:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And in a very strange way, because we\Nspent so much time with one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.16,0:12:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We helped raise...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.67,0:12:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.04,0:12:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a camaraderie\Nbetween these students
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.47,0:12:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that I don't know that I've seen since
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.13,0:12:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I left this school.\NI can remember, and I won't say names,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.98,0:12:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,there was a student that went here
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.98,0:12:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that used to sell drugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.77,0:12:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't just a student,\Nbut this particular guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.78,0:13:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This particular guy did the cardinal no-no\Non the streets. He did what they call
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.08,0:13:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,"not making your roll," which meant he\Ngot some drugs on consignment
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.75,0:13:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and he didn't pay whoever\Ngave him the drugs back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.34,0:13:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And whoever gave him those drugs\Nhad declared,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.41,0:13:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'm gonna come to that school,\Nand I'm gonna kill you," he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.10,0:13:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And my man was scared,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.42,0:13:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and word got around,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.63,0:13:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,around school,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.26,0:13:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that the goons was coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.60,0:13:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And by the time the goons showed up,\Nevery dude that went to this school:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.44,0:13:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,gay, straight, whatever the fuck,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.49,0:13:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,was all standing out front, they say,\N"You'll have to kill all of us."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.08,0:13:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And who was in front of all of 'em?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.62,0:13:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger Bellamy with some\Nleg warmers on like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.86,0:14:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I started making friends that are still\Nmy friends to this very day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.74,0:14:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Life-long friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.07,0:14:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,As I get older, I appreciate my teachers\Nmore and more.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.12,0:14:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But to tell you the truth,\NI appreciated them then.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.28,0:14:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Teacher salaries, you know,\Nnot necessarily what it should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.91,0:14:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I think about that,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.17,0:14:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,juxtaposed to the dedication
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.88,0:14:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that the teachers, the time they would\Nspend with me, the way they would notice,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.10,0:14:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,"Are you okay? Is everything all right?\NYou look sad today."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.01,0:14:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Any little thing,\Nlike a family member would.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.44,0:14:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And they fostered an environment\Nof almost absolute trust,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.27,0:14:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,like your parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.11,0:15:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,There's two lectures that I got at school
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.27,0:15:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that changed the way I do comedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.95,0:15:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That like...\Nturned the light switch on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.12,0:15:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It was two teachers:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.33,0:15:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Donal Leace.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.50,0:15:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Donal Leace, may he rest in peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.62,0:15:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe one of the single best educators\Nthat I've ever met in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.60,0:15:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He had a demeanor about himself that\Ndemanded excellence from his students.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.98,0:15:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He would tell us incredible stories\Nthat I didn't believe. He claimed...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.32,0:15:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in one class, the song "Killing\NHim Softly" was about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.32,0:15:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I was like, "Nah, nigga, not you."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.15,0:15:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He told me he knew Donny Hathaway\Nand Roberta Flack and all these people.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.28,0:15:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,These D.C. legends.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.28,0:15:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a humble man, but he really\Ndemanded excellence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.00,0:16:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And he gave us a lecture once\Non a concept called polarization.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.59,0:16:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Polarization meaning the--\Nthe idea that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.97,0:16:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,if you can make everybody\Nlook at the same thing
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.51,0:16:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,at the same time, that their\Nrational mind will decrease,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.14,0:16:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and their emotional response\Nwill increase.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.07,0:16:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, "That's how audiences work,\Nthat's how mobs work,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.64,0:16:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that's how you make a person lose\Nthemself in the crowd."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.27,0:16:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.95,0:16:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,As he was saying this, he would hold\Na stapler in his hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.50,0:16:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it was a good lecture. He said,\N"Everyone focus on the stapler,"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.78,0:16:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and he would explain to us\Nwhat polarization is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.53,0:16:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,as we're all looking at this stapler,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.91,0:16:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and then he'd scream, "Hah!"\NAnd everyone would jump, "Oh!"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.12,0:16:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, "What're you scared of?"\N"Oh, shit, that works."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.50,0:16:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And ever since he did that lecture,\NI listened in his class intently.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.38,0:16:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He was one of the only guys that I would\Nalways get straight As from
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.26,0:16:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because I worked very hard, not to get his\Napproval, but to avoid his disapproval.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.07,0:17:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,When we were coming up,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.49,0:17:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,they had a thing called juries.\NI don't know, do they still do juries?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.52,0:17:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Juries is when all the department heads\Ngive you a piece to work on,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.95,0:17:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and they sit there, and they make you\Nperform the piece,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.96,0:17:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and the criticism is brutal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.13,0:17:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And we were kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.17,0:17:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't understand that they were\Npreparing us for a hard world ahead
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.22,0:17:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,if you wanted a profession in art.\NThey would tear us to shreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.05,0:17:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Just the stress...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.48,0:17:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The stress of a jury.\NAnd man, I never practiced.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.77,0:17:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,'Cause I didn't wanna act.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.49,0:17:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,At an improv class, a teacher named\NGeraldine Gillstrap told me
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.24,0:17:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that she should-- I should\Nstop doing funny pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.70,0:17:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That I should try to stretch\Nmyself artistically.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.50,0:17:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And maybe had more in me than comedy.\NAnd at the time, I took offense to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.58,0:18:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So because she said that,\Nafter school that very night,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.22,0:18:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to the comedy club,\Nand for the first time I signed the list,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.89,0:18:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and I waited, and I got on,\Nand I killed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.26,0:18:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Killed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.26,0:18:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Must have been 35 years ago,\Nnight after night, I killed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.23,0:18:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd show up with the bag of tricks\Nthat I learned at school,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.19,0:18:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and I would dominate adults\Non a regular basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.57,0:18:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Couldn't wait to get out of D.C.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.61,0:18:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was 17,\NI moved to New York
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.21,0:18:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and lit that comedy scene up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.33,0:18:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I was obviously talented. You'll hear\Nstories about people saying
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.58,0:18:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that I discovered Dave Chappelle. That's\Nlike saying you discovered sunshine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.08,0:18:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I was shining on everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.23,0:19:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I got in that professional world,\NI was oddly prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.35,0:19:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a sense of professionalism,\NI showed up on time,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.81,0:19:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I did the things that I learned in school\Nto do. Just the basics.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.74,0:19:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,My... career didn't have any direction\N'cause I was still so young.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.75,0:19:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And that didn't change for many years.\NIt didn't change until, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.03,0:19:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,my girlfriend at the time, now my wife,\Ntold me she was pregnant,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.04,0:19:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was like, "You know what? I should\Nreally start taking this seriously."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.50,0:19:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And when she told me that, before the baby\Nwas born, I'd done my first HBO special,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.19,0:19:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and then-- and then I went to work on\Na sketch comedy show idea I had, and--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.94,0:19:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and-- and The Chappelle Show came out
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.35,0:19:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,when my son was still\Nmaybe 18 months-year old.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.32,0:19:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And I bet on myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.25,0:19:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I took less money. I took less money,\NI remember that,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.42,0:20:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,so I could do what I wanted to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.86,0:20:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, "You don't have to pay me\Nthat much, but you can't ever tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.50,0:20:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't ever tell me that I can't do\Nwhat I wanna do."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.29,0:20:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did the first season,\NI'll tell you, for $300,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.04,0:20:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Which sounds like a lot of money,\Nbut-- but-- but-- but-- but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.48,0:20:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a rare experience in my life,\Nbecause it was the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.40,0:20:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that I did something\Nthat was so successful
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.44,0:20:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that I knew I had exceeded\Nthe expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.70,0:20:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I was more successful\Nthan I felt like I was supposed to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.27,0:20:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't plan on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.95,0:20:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The second season...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.32,0:20:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,came out, and it was a juggernaut,\Nand-- and-- and...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.96,0:20:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and then, I remember this was\Nthe single best day of my career,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.42,0:20:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the Rick James episode of Chappelle Show\Nhad come out...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.47,0:20:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,People were going crazy about\Nthe Rick James episode at the same time
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.72,0:21:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the-- the DVD for Season 1 of Chappelle\NShow dropped. It was the first time any
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.30,0:21:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,television show had ever\Nbeen sold off air.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.44,0:21:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And it sold a million copies\Nin the first day. It was unheard of.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.77,0:21:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,To this day, nothing has sold more\Nthan Chappelle Show.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.74,0:21:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still on the Top Ten in Netflix.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.20,0:21:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,All those great things happened,\Nand my contract was up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.82,0:21:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Clearly...\NClearly, I was about to be rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.75,0:21:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll spare you all the details\Nof why it didn't work out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.00,0:21:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But it didn't work out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.75,0:21:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And I ended up doing something that no one\Nhad ever seen before, including myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.51,0:21:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe Prince is the only other guy\Nthat I've seen do this,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.84,0:21:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,where you just quit something that was\Npopular when you're at the very top of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.10,0:21:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucky for me, when I quit,\NI went to Africa,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.49,0:21:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,so there was a media storm\Nthat I didn't hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.95,0:22:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time I got back, everyone\Nwas just lookin' at me crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.03,0:22:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a very difficult\Ndecision to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.67,0:22:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire world told me I was crazy,\Nbut I-- I was sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.58,0:22:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sure I was being true to myself and\Nto something that I learned at Ellington.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.23,0:22:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm one of those comedians\Nthat thought of himself as an artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.23,0:22:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I was enamored by what the genre could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.31,0:22:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like... the pictures\Nthat I could paint with words, and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.85,0:22:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the way I could engage with audiences.\NI understood as it was happening,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.91,0:22:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I was very lucky to be able to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.45,0:22:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And I protected that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.41,0:22:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And I knew that if I took the money,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.11,0:22:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,they would expect me\Nto behave differently,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.53,0:22:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and I wasn't willing to accept that,\Nso I quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.63,0:22:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I quit, it was a very difficult\Ntime in my life,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.13,0:22:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'll spare you the details, but man,\Nfuck show business. It was tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.39,0:23:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And then one day I was\Nin Panama City, Panama,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.01,0:23:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was in a hotel,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.98,0:23:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and I looked at the lobby, there was\Na-- a painting of Abraham Lincoln.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.31,0:23:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Was-- And then-- I would look closer,\Nit wasn't a painting, it was all pennies,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.60,0:23:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,just pennies on a black canvas,\Narranged into the face of Abraham Lincoln.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.95,0:23:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And I asked the guy, I said,\N"How much is that painting worth?"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.57,0:23:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, "$600,000, sir."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.28,0:23:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And I looked at the pennies\Nthat made up the painting,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.67,0:23:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was like,\N"That's like, $300 worth of pennies."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.29,0:23:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Lightbulb went in my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.58,0:23:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized the value of art.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.05,0:23:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of the biggest wars and crimes\Nand scams in history
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.30,0:23:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,were financed through the theft of art.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.48,0:23:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Art is a powerful commodity.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.69,0:24:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,An artist, if you're good at it,\Nshould never behave as a commodity.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.99,0:24:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a tough one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.57,0:24:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I gave up.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.13,0:24:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,'Cause it-- I said, "Oh--\Nyou know, this is probably it."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.71,0:24:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I accepted the fact that the career\NI thought I was gonna have was over, but,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.14,0:24:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I started to rediscover just my art\Nfor its own sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.72,0:24:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I would go to comedy clubs and I'd work\Nfor way less money than I ever had,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.19,0:24:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and I enjoyed it more\Nthan any of the work I ever did.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.23,0:24:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It was probably the best work\NI'll ever do.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.60,0:24:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,'Cause it was so honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.02,0:24:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It was so sincere.\NThere was no media,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.02,0:24:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,there was no studio,\Nthere was no scrutiny,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.61,0:24:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,just me and the crowds. And I did it\Nnight after night, and slowly but surely
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.00,0:24:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the crowds got bigger and bigger, and then\Nsuddenly people started to notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.61,0:24:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In post, I would say, "Dave Chappelle\Nhas the tour of the year."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.08,0:25:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And again, and then the year after that,\Nand then the year after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.22,0:25:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And then,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.68,0:25:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Lorne Michaels
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.47,0:25:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,asked me to do Saturday Night Live.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.30,0:25:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And it wasn't just like he asked me,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.19,0:25:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,he was courtin' me, I didn't even know it,\Nhe gave me this whole long speech,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.98,0:25:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was like, "All right." And then\NI read some book about Lorne Michaels
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.31,0:25:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,starting Saturday Night Live, and I read\Nthe speech that he gave Richard Pryor
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.24,0:25:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,when he wanted him to host the show,\Nand I said, "Holy shit,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.16,0:25:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the same shit he said to me!"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.00,0:25:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.50,0:25:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was an enormous amount\Nof pressure, it had been 12 years
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.63,0:25:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,since I'd been on television,\Nor since I'd even talked to the media,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.17,0:25:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and I remember I signed my Netflix\Ncontract on my way to my mark
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.50,0:25:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,for the monologue. If you do live\Ntelevision, they count down every second,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.55,0:25:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,"30 seconds..."\N"Are you sure this contract is good?"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.80,0:25:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,"It's good, just sign the papers..."\N"22 seconds..."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.55,0:25:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,"Aw, nigga, you better not\Nbe trickin' me."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.56,0:26:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten, nine, eight, seven, six, five, four,\Nthree, two, one,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.52,0:26:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I walked out on that stage,\Nand I killed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.52,0:26:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It was natural. It was nothing.\NIt was easy work.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.00,0:26:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Got an Emmy for that one, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.50,0:26:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,First Emmy I won.\NAnd when I walked on the stage
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.29,0:26:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,after being in the cold for so long,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.29,0:26:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,for the first time when I walked\Non the stage, I'm like,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.18,0:26:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,"Damn, nigga, I just made\N60 million dollars."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.54,0:26:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I thought to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.18,0:26:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been great ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.85,0:26:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And really I could do these specials like\NSteph Curry, I be shooting from inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.40,0:26:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,outside, all night.\NIt's been great ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.66,0:26:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of my friends are athletes,\Nand I never could understand
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.86,0:26:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,what it would feel like
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.00,0:27:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to only have a limited amount of time to\Nbe great. You got 20 years to be the best,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.08,0:27:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,or 30 years to be the best,\Nbut when you do art, you could be great
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.33,0:27:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,whenever the will decides\Nthat you're great.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.29,0:27:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And I feel very lucky for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.43,0:27:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And I never forgot this school.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.59,0:27:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I've always come back,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.05,0:27:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,checked in. One of my favorite honors\Nwas doing the commencement at Ellington.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.98,0:27:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, I can't even remember\Nwhat year it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.15,0:27:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I just remember they cheered for me\Nwhen I came out, I wasn't a big star,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.81,0:27:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but I was their star,\Nand I felt like I was home.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.67,0:27:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,After I did Lorne Michaels,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.71,0:27:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, after I did Saturday Night Live,\NLorne Michaels said something that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.25,0:27:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I gotta share with you. He goes,\N"You went to Peggy Cafritz's school,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.58,0:27:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't you?" That's what he said.\NI said, "I did," and he said... he said--
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.22,0:27:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to say this on\NSaturday Night Live. He goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.09,0:27:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,"Tell her I owe her money."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.85,0:28:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.90,0:28:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I never asked\Nto have this theater named after me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.70,0:28:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Peggy asked me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.02,0:28:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,She was ailing, and I went\Nto her house to visit her.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.82,0:28:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And she said, "I want you to put your name\Non the school," she said,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.95,0:28:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,"It would help us raise money\Nfor the school," and to me, it was like,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.66,0:28:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like I'm a little young for that,\Nand I'm still kind of using the name,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.17,0:28:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.75,0:28:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see what I do with it first!\NYou never know...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.50,0:28:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, imagine if O.J. had named\Nhis son O.J. Junior.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.50,0:28:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh, Dad!"
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.73,0:28:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And around then, I was receiving\Nthe Mark Twain Prize. Huge honor...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.44,0:28:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,-And...\N-[audience applauds]
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.77,0:28:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next day, all the artists\Nthat came to honor me,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.36,0:29:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bradley Coopers and Chris Tuckers,\Nand all these great people who
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.07,0:29:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,came to Ellington and they taught\Nmaster classes for the students.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.21,0:29:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And Peggy Cooper Cafritz,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.04,0:29:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,as sick as she was,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.68,0:29:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,got out of her bed,\Nso she could be with her babies.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.30,0:29:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She never left us.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.51,0:29:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So I did it. So, you know, whatever you\Nwanna do, if I can help,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.60,0:29:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.15,0:29:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I have to tell you:
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.81,0:29:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,if you quit a show like Chappelle Show,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.16,0:29:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if you know what\Nhappens to you professionally,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.49,0:29:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'll tell you what doesn't happen.\NThey don't just say,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.36,0:29:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,"Well, good luck\Nin your future endeavors."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.17,0:29:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,With that media, they beat me up.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.92,0:29:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,With their power,\Nthey tried to make me behave, it's--
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.96,0:29:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,-it-- it takes a strong person...\N-[audience member] Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.08,0:29:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,...to stand out in the cold like that,\Nand I swear to God,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.04,0:30:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,so much of the strength I got to do that,\Nthe inner warmth I got to do that,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.01,0:30:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned in this school,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.09,0:30:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and from my friends\Nwho helped raise me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.19,0:30:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So why wouldn't...\NI'd do anything I could
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.74,0:30:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to help my benefactor.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.95,0:30:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And the last time I came back,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.71,0:30:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,after The Closer,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.42,0:30:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,when the kids were mad at me,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.08,0:30:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I got to tell you,\Nthat was quite the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.83,0:30:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All the kids was screaming and yelling,\NI remember, I said to the kids, I go,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.58,0:30:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,"Well, okay, well what do you guys\Nthink I did wrong?"
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.93,0:30:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And a line formed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.94,0:30:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,These kids said everything about gender,\Nand this and that and the other,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.15,0:30:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but they didn't say anything about art.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.36,0:31:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is my biggest gripe
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.49,0:31:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,with this whole controversy with\NThe Closer: that you cannot report
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.41,0:31:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,on an artist's work, and remove\Nartistic nuance from his words.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.58,0:31:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be like if you were reading\Na newspaper and they say,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.25,0:31:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,"Man Shot in the Face by a Six-Foot Rabbit\NExpected to Survive," you'd be like
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.84,0:31:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh, my God," and they never tell you\Nit's a Bugs Bunny cartoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.56,0:31:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I took a lot of cold shots...\Nin show business.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.11,0:31:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And I gotta tell you, as the years go on,\Nyou feel the shots less and less.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.82,0:31:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,"Ah, it's just the business,"\Nis what you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.17,0:31:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But that one, that day,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.28,0:31:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,boy, that day they hurt me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.58,0:31:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,When I heard those talking points\Ncoming out of these children's faces,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.79,0:32:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that really, sincerely, hurt me.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.00,0:32:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I know those kids didn't\Ncome up with those words,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.89,0:32:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard those words before.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.85,0:32:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The more you say I can't say something,\Nthe more urgent it is for me to say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.16,0:32:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And it has nothing to do\Nwith what you're saying I can't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.57,0:32:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It has everything to do with my right,\Nmy freedom...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.20,0:32:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,of artistic expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.36,0:32:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That is valuable to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.83,0:32:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That is not severed from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.50,0:32:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's worth protecting for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.88,0:32:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's\Nworth protecting for everyone else
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.93,0:32:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,who endeavors in our noble,\Nnoble professions.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.39,0:32:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And these kids...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.23,0:32:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And these kids didn't understand\Nthat they were instruments...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.69,0:32:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,instruments of oppression.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.65,0:33:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And I didn't get mad at them.\NThey're kids. They're freshmen.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.31,0:33:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not ready yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.56,0:33:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.91,0:33:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What made me mad...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.74,0:33:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and I am this petty...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.33,0:33:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I ain't sayin' names.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.96,0:33:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the kid's mother went on Fox News,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.50,0:33:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and she used to be a student here,\NI remember her face
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.43,0:33:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but I don't know if she was\Nparticularly popular. Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.48,0:33:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,She was in\Nthe Literary Media Arts department.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.49,0:33:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,She said a lot of things\Nthat I didn't like, lot of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.95,0:33:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But, you know, that's her right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.28,0:33:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing she said that got to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.00,0:33:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,she said, "At Duke Ellington, that theater\Nwas a sanctuary for students.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.03,0:34:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to sit there and meditate."\NWell, of course you'd meditate.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.21,0:34:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You were a Literary Media Arts student.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.39,0:34:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't meditate in here.\NWe got to work. But, okay, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.96,0:34:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,"I would sit in there and meditate,"\Nshe said.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.44,0:34:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And then she scrunched her face up.\NShe's a beautiful woman,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.86,0:34:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but her face looked hideous,\Nthe way she scrunched it up,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.82,0:34:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and she said, "And just to imagine...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.78,0:34:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,his name...\Non that theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.50,0:34:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,How could you do that to those kids?"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.80,0:34:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.84,0:34:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what they said\Nabout The Closer,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.76,0:34:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it was still the most-watched\Nspecial in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.51,0:35:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And I am still of the mind,\Nand I say this with all humility,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.36,0:35:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it is a masterpiece, and I challenge\Nall my p-- my peers-- to make its equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.73,0:35:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They cannot. I am sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.00,0:35:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It will be decades before you ever see\Nsomeone in my genre
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.63,0:35:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,as proficient as me.\NI am maybe a once-in-a-lifetime talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.17,0:35:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I am telling you the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.09,0:35:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,About three weeks ago I saw\Nin the newspaper that a man,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.01,0:35:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,they said a man that was dressed\Nin women's clothing,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.57,0:35:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,threw a-- a pie at the Mona Lisa\Nand tried to deface it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.32,0:35:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And-- and it made me laugh,\N'cause I'm like, "It's like The Closer."
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.67,0:36:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I said it to the kids that day: if you\Nhave a better idea, then express it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.67,0:36:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can beat me. It's that easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.09,0:36:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have more talent than me,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.17,0:36:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,then display it and you can beat me
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.26,0:36:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,with certainty.\NThis is what our genre is about.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.26,0:36:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea that my name will be turned into
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.26,0:36:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a-- a-- a instrument of someone else's\Nperceived oppression
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.65,0:36:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is untenable to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.15,0:36:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that if my name was\Non this theater, and a kid
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.03,0:36:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that walked through that door would feel\Nanything other than pride in his school
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.78,0:36:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and in their endeavors,\Nthat's untenable to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.17,0:36:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So on Friday, I decided...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.84,0:36:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that I don't want my name on the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.84,0:36:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hear me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.21,0:36:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The Ellington family is my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.55,0:36:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,When this controversy came out,\Nand students were angry,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.76,0:37:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,at the height of their anger,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.23,0:37:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,they said, "We still wanna name\Nthe theater after you."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.09,0:37:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They taught the kids about the nuance\Nof art and activism.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.73,0:37:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And to-- I feel a great deal of success,\Nand it came around.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.44,0:37:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not that they did not wanna give\Nthis to me, they're still my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.90,0:37:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And, I'm not gonna say I don't want it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.36,0:37:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna say I'll defer it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.82,0:37:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than give this theater my name,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.28,0:37:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to give these students\Nmy message.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.63,0:37:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,To them.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.59,0:37:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So it is with great honor, that I unveil\Nthe new name of this theater,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.30,0:37:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the Jerrod Carmichael Theater.\NI'm just kidding, I'm just kiddin'...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.19,0:37:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just kiddin'.\NI'm totally joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.15,0:37:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, let me see if I can get this here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.82,0:37:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This theater should be called...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.36,0:37:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The Theater\Nfor Artistic Freedom and Expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.19,0:38:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I want that for myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.11,0:38:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and I want it for every student\Nthat's educated at this school.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.88,0:38:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And when and if you are ever ready,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.09,0:38:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you can put my name right on top of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.42,0:38:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I love you, Duke Ellington, thank you\Nvery much. Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.21,0:38:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.23,0:38:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen, it is my pleasure\Nto bring off his new album Leace Renewed,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.26,0:38:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the first single "Flow to You,"\Ngive it up for the best-hitter
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.07,0:38:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,history teacher in the world, Mr. Leace.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.11,0:38:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughter from class]
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.69,0:38:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,[Mr. Leace and students singing]
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.26,0:39:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,[students begin clapping]
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.61,0:39:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on! Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.71,0:39:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,[all clapping]
